"use strict";(self.webpackChunkepinio_docusaurus=self.webpackChunkepinio_docusaurus||[]).push([[11477],{30010:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"epinio-1-14-0","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-14-0","source":"@site/blog/2026-05-29-epinio-1-14-0.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.14.0!","description":"We have been teasing this release for a while, and the 1.13.X series was laying the","date":"2026-05-29T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 29, 2026","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-14-0","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.14.0!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2026-05-29T00:00:00.000Z"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.10!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-10"}},"content":"We have been teasing this release for a while, and the 1.13.X series was laying the\\ngroundwork for exactly this moment. 1.14.0 is here, and it delivers the Epinio UI\\noverhaul, major performance improvements, and a long list of features and fixes\\nacross the board.\\n\\nCustomers currently on a prior release are encouraged to review the documentation\\nfor updates and [breaking changes](https://docs.epinio.io/reference/upgrading). You can also schedule time with us to review these updates.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## New features and improvements\\n\\n- Applications now deploy in the background \u2014 leave the page once you kick off a deploy and let Epinio handle the rest.\\n- Server-side search and pagination across application and resource tables to increase client performance.\\n- Application deployment progress is now visible via the notifications panel.\\n- Epinio can now be installed in [namespaces other than](https://docs.epinio.io/installation/install_epinio#install-epinio-in-a-custom-namespace) `epinio`.\\n- Default token expiry is [now configurable](https://docs.epinio.io/installation/install_epinio#server-configuration).\\n- Improved performance via the `KUBE_API_QPS` and `KUBE_API_BURST` environment variables.\\n\\n## UI\\n\\nThis release delivers the full Trailhand design system rollout across Epinio. Every\\nmajor area of the UI has been updated, including applications, services,\\nconfigurations, catalog, and the about page. This also lets us move much quicker on\\nfuture updates to the UI and backend, now that we are less restricted by legacy UI\\ncomponents.\\n\\n- Application creation and editing now use a streamlined modal flow.\\n- Service detail pages now show internal paths.\\n- Namespace column added to the services and configuration tables.\\n- Removed the redundant \\"Show Configuration\\" feature from the Rancher Extension.\\n- Added UI guards to match the backend permission guards.\\n\\n## Maintenance and fixes\\n\\n- Fixed service bindings taking too long to complete.\\n- Fixed application creation error messages not displaying correctly.\\n- Fixed inconsistent column spacing across namespace tables.\\n- Fixed Dex login issues when multiple clusters are present in the Rancher Extension.\\n- Improved application creation progress step copy for clarity.\\n- Allow rebuild to succeed with missing resources when there is a git source.\\n\\n## Documentation updates\\n\\n- We started the process of reorganizing and adding additional documentation.\\n- [Added documentation around the](https://docs.epinio.io/howtos/other/performance_tuning) `KUBE_API_QPS` and `KUBE_API_BURST` performance variables.\\n\\n## Dependency updates\\n\\n- Bumped Dex to v2.45.1.\\n- Bumped dozens of dependencies.\\n\\n## Epinio MCP (experimental)\\n\\nWe recently made an early version of the [Epinio MCP server available](https://github.com/epinio/mcp). Note that this is still experimental, and we will update you all as it becomes stable.\\n\\n---\\n\\nFor the complete technical changelog, see the\\n[1.14.0 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.14.0)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-10","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-10","source":"@site/blog/2026-04-10-epinio-1-13-10.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.10!","description":"Customers currently on a prior release are encouraged to review the documentation","date":"2026-04-10T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 10, 2026","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-10","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.10!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2026-04-10T00:00:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.14.0!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-14-0"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.9!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-9"}},"content":"Customers currently on a prior release are encouraged to review the documentation\\nfor updates and [breaking changes](https://docs.epinio.io/reference/upgrading). You can also schedule time with us to review these updates.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## New features and improvements\\n\\n- Added additional role options and default roles.\\n- Several loading-time performance improvements.\\n- **UI**\\n  - Rancher Extension Epinio one-click install.\\n  - Added a Cluster Metrics Report download feature under System \u2192 About.\\n\\n## Maintenance and fixes\\n\\n- Replaced MinIO with SeaweedFS.\\n- Fixed several form updating and saving issues under certain conditions.\\n- Fixed service bindings being wiped out when an application is redeployed.\\n- Switched the Dex version for full OIDC support.\\n- Bumped the default timeout limit for various long-running tasks.\\n- Replaced SPDY with Kubernetes-native websockets.\\n- Dependency updates.\\n\\n---\\n\\nFor the complete technical changelog, see the\\n[1.13.10 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.10)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-9","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-9","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-03-epinio-1-13-9.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.9!","description":"Epinio 1.13.9 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.","date":"2026-02-03T10:09:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 3, 2026","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-9","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.9!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2026-02-03T10:09:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.10!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-10"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.8!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-8"}},"content":"Epinio 1.13.9 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.\\n\\nFor the full list of changes, see the\\n[1.13.9 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.9)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-8","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-8","source":"@site/blog/2026-02-03-epinio-1-13-8.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.8!","description":"This release continues our focus on performance, security improvements, and bug","date":"2026-02-03T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 3, 2026","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-8","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.8!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2026-02-03T00:00:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.9!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-9"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.7!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-7"}},"content":"This release continues our focus on performance, security improvements, and bug\\nfixes. We were also able to squeeze a few new features in.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## New features and improvements\\n\\n- Added the `app_restart` action to the permissions set, to allow the functionality without write permissions.\\n- Added parallel binding to speed up service-binding wait times.\\n- Moved to a new centralized logging system.\\n- Improved websocket performance for log viewing.\\n- **CLI**\\n  - Use `--no-restart` to update an application without triggering a restart.\\n  - Delete an image from the Epinio registry with the `--delete-image` flag.\\n  - [Ignore certain files](https://docs.epinio.io/references/ignore-files) on app push via `.epinioignore` or the `configuration.ignore` section of your Epinio manifest.\\n- **UI**\\n  - Filter by container, tail, since, and since-time in the App and Build Logs widget.\\n  - Delete an image from the Epinio registry via a checkbox when deleting an application.\\n  - Download a log bundle for the Epinio instance, with the option to include or exclude application logs.\\n\\n## Maintenance and fixes\\n\\n- Replaced kubed with reflector.\\n- Fixed an issue where environment variables conflicted with Epinio manifest variables.\\n- Fixed several UI forms not loading data correctly.\\n- Fixed the application page not showing proper information when instances are scaled to 0.\\n- Fixed MinIO and Dex privilege-escalation issues.\\n\\n---\\n\\nFor the complete technical changelog, see the\\n[1.13.8 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.8)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-7","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-7","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-15-epinio-1-13-7.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.7!","description":"Epinio 1.13.7 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.","date":"2025-12-15T10:07:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 15, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-7","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.7!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-12-15T10:07:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.8!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-8"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.6!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-6"}},"content":"Epinio 1.13.7 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.\\n\\nFor the full list of changes, see the\\n[1.13.7 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.7)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-6","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-6","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-15-epinio-1-13-6.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.6!","description":"Epinio 1.13.6 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.","date":"2025-12-15T10:06:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 15, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-6","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.6!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-12-15T10:06:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.7!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-7"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.5!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-5"}},"content":"Epinio 1.13.6 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.\\n\\nFor the full list of changes, see the\\n[1.13.6 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.6)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-5","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-5","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-15-epinio-1-13-5.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.5!","description":"Customers currently on a prior release are encouraged to review the breaking changes documentation. You can also schedule time with us to review these updates.","date":"2025-12-15T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 15, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-5","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.5!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-12-15T00:00:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.6!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-6"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.4!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-4"}},"content":"Customers currently on a prior release are encouraged to review the [breaking changes](https://docs.epinio.io/reference/upgrading) documentation. You can also schedule time with us to review these updates.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Helm chart enhancements\\n\\n- Updated Bitnami packages.\\n- Node selector support for the Helm controller.\\n- ServiceAccount annotation support for the Epinio server.\\n- Additional deployment configuration options for the Epinio UI.\\n\\n## Performance enhancements\\n\\n- New centralized logger (we\'ll migrate fully to this in 1.13.6).\\n- Service bindings, especially multiple bindings, now run in parallel.\\n- Server support for tailing and date-time filtering of logs (UI support coming in 1.13.6).\\n\\n## UI and CLI changes\\n\\n- The new user experience has been designed, and we\'ve begun implementing components. This reforms how the UI looks (while staying familiar) and improves performance over the next few updates up to 1.14.0.\\n- Dark/light mode toggle.\\n- Updated table component using our new design system, including client-side pagination (server-side pagination coming in 1.13.6).\\n- CLI logging improvements and general bug fixes.\\n- Several bug fixes around buttons and form flow.\\n\\n## Dependency and security updates\\n\\nThis release also includes a range of dependency and security updates.\\n\\n---\\n\\nFor the complete technical changelog, see the\\n[1.13.5 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.5)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-4","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-4","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-11-epinio-1-13-4.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.4!","description":"Epinio 1.13.4 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.","date":"2025-12-11T10:04:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 11, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-4","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.4!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-12-11T10:04:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.5!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-5"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.3!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-3"}},"content":"Epinio 1.13.4 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.\\n\\nFor the full list of changes, see the\\n[1.13.4 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.4)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-3","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-3","source":"@site/blog/2025-12-11-epinio-1-13-3.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.3!","description":"Epinio 1.13.3 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.","date":"2025-12-11T10:03:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 11, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-3","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.3!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-12-11T10:03:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.4!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-4"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.2!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-2"}},"content":"Epinio 1.13.3 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.\\n\\nFor the full list of changes, see the\\n[1.13.3 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.3)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-2","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-2","source":"@site/blog/2025-10-27-epinio-1-13-2.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.2!","description":"Epinio 1.13.2 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.","date":"2025-10-27T10:02:00.000Z","formattedDate":"October 27, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-2","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.2!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-10-27T10:02:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.3!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-3"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.1!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-1"}},"content":"Epinio 1.13.2 is a maintenance release with bug fixes and dependency updates.\\n\\nFor the full list of changes, see the\\n[1.13.2 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.2)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-1","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-1","source":"@site/blog/2025-09-29-epinio-1-13-1.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.1!","description":"Epinio 1.13.1 is a UI maintenance release.","date":"2025-09-29T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 29, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-1","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.1!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-09-29T00:00:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.2!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-2"},"nextItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.0!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-0"}},"content":"Epinio 1.13.1 is a UI maintenance release.\\n\\n- Fixed the application create button.\\n\\nFor the full list of changes, see the\\n[1.13.1 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/ui/releases/tag/v1.13.1)."},{"id":"epinio-1-13-0","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-0","source":"@site/blog/2025-09-24-epinio-1-13-0.md","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.0!","description":"Customers currently on a prior release are encouraged to review the breaking changes documentation. You can also schedule time with us to review","date":"2025-09-24T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 24, 2025","tags":[{"label":"release","permalink":"/blog/tags/release"}],"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"The Epinio Team","title":"Epinio Maintainers","url":"https://github.com/epinio","imageURL":"https://github.com/epinio.png","key":"epinio"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"epinio-1-13-0","title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.0!","authors":["epinio"],"tags":["release"],"date":"2025-09-24T00:00:00.000Z"},"prevItem":{"title":"Announcing Epinio 1.13.1!","permalink":"/blog/epinio-1-13-1"}},"content":"Customers currently on a prior release are encouraged to review the [breaking changes](https://docs.epinio.io/reference/upgrading) documentation. You can also schedule time with us to review\\nthese updates.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Highlights\\n\\n- Storage configurability for staging via Helm charts.\\n- Staging scheduling configurability via Helm charts.\\n- Dependency updates for the Epinio server and Epinio UI.\\n- Epinio UI fixes and cleanup for Rancher 2.12.0+.\\n- Documentation updates for the storage and scheduling capabilities.\\n\\n---\\n\\nFor the complete technical changelog, see the\\n[1.13.0 release on GitHub](https://github.com/epinio/epinio/releases/tag/v1.13.0)."}]}')}}]);